    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Domini Dei Salvatoris nostri Iesu Christi. Domnus <persName
                            ref="#people/303" key="#Princeps #Marquis/duke">Arichis</persName>
                        piissimus atque excellentissimus <rs key="#Princeps">princeps</rs> gentis
                        Langubardorum, divino premonitus nutu, offero in <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/85"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Churches #Monasteries"><rs key="#Churches"
                                >ecclesia</rs> Sancte Sophie</orgName> quam a fundamentis edificavi,
                        pro redemptione anime meę seu pro salvatione gentis nostre et patrię,
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3414"><rs key="#Churches">ęcclesiam</rs> Sancti
                            Mercurii</orgName> que posita est in <geogName ref="#estates/3407"
                            key="#Gai #Fiscal_property"><rs key="#Gai">gaio</rs> nostro
                            Fęcline</geogName> et de ipso gaio circa ipsam ecclesiam largiti sumus
                        in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> Sancte Sophię <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>
                        <rs key="#Size">modiorum quingenta</rs>; seu et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3415"><rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> Sancte
                            Reparatę</orgName> que in ipso <rs key="#Gai">gaio</rs> posita est,
                        nostra vero potestas concessit in <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        Sancte Sophię <rs key="#Landed_possessions">territorio</rs> quantum <rs
                            key="#Priests">presbyter</rs> ipsius ęcclesię <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Inflow #Confiscation #Property_of_criminals/political_traitors"
                            >sine palatii concessione</rs> tenebat. Quod vero preceptum oblationis
                        ex iussione et dictatu nominate potestatis scripsi ego <persName
                            ref="#people/3410" key="#Notary">Lopoald</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>. Actus <placeName key="#Cities"
                            ref="#places/110">Beneventus</placeName> in filicissimus palatio in anno
                        septimo decimo, mensi novembrio per indictione tertiam decimam.
                        Feliciter.</ab>
                    <note>
                        <ab>Nel cartulario è presente anche un riassunto del documento, inserito nel
                            falso <foreign>preceptum donationum, concessionum et
                                confirmationum</foreign> del novembre 774 (CSS, (†) I, 1, pp.
                            289-336), per il quale si veda il commento al doc. 3535. Segue il testo
                            di detto riassunto (CSS, I, 1 [4], p. 294):</ab>
                    </note> <ab>(…) [4] Nec non et ecclesia Sancti Mercurii 
                            que posita est in gaio nostro Fecline et de ipso gaio circa ipsa ecclesia 
                            largiti sumus terra modiorum quingenta. Seu et ecclesia Sancte Reparate 
                            que in ipso gaio posita est, nostra vero potestas concessit in monasterio 
                            Sancte Sophie territoria modiorum centum. (…)</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p><emph>Editions</emph>: IS1 VIII, col. 582; IS2 X-2, col. 429; Borgia 1763-1769,
